## Template / Standards Takeaways

- Add lighting section to both learning and generated-scene verification templates.
- Detect lighting recursively by definition/material names: `подсвет`, `light`, `diffuser`, `4000k/5000k/6000k/7000k`, `Врезной профиль`.
- Do not classify all top-level countertop components as worktops; split horizontal worktops from vertical backsplash/upstand by orientation and bbox.
- Treat standalone fridge as real component evidence, not an EK module and not a measurement proxy.
- Recognize L corners assembled without `BG1` when the finished project uses filler/blend/countertop joinery instead of a lower corner cabinet.
- Keep detached sample/island blocks separate from main kitchen row analysis.

